I've created a minimum example of this error - the issue appears to be that `TestFixtureSource` doesn't work with generic classes. The below reproduces the crash with NUnit 3.2.

```
    [TestFixtureSource("SupportedEnumerableTypesForDeserialization")]
    public class ArrayTestCase<T>
    {
        private string _aString;

        public ArrayTestCase(string aString)
        {
            _aString = aString;
        }

        [Test]
        public void Test()
        {
            Assert.That(_aString, Is.EqualTo("Something"));
        }

        public static IEnumerable<string> SupportedEnumerableTypesForDeserialization
        {
            get
            {
                yield return "TestCase";
            }
       }
    }
```

Additionally verified that the console returns zero on this crash - as it's at test-suite level, and only invalid assemblies, or individual tests are counted towards the return code. That seems like a separate issue - I'll create another.

issue.body:
Separated out from #1346, if the console encounters invalid test suites, it still returns zero. Invalid assemblies and invalid tests contribute to the return code, but not invalid test suites.

Should we add an additional return code for this? -3 FIXTURE_NOT_FOUND currently appears to be unused - what was the intention of that, for invalid filtering?

```
public static readonly int OK = 0;
public static readonly int INVALID_ARG = -1;
public static readonly int INVALID_ASSEMBLY = -2;
public static readonly int FIXTURE_NOT_FOUND = -3;
public static readonly int UNEXPECTED_ERROR = -100;
```

