**NOTE**: This is based on `mw-uninterpret`: that should be merged first?

This mainly refactoring PRQ:
- Removes `Unmarked`: every instance where a variable could be unmarked now has this reflected in the variable type (`Var` vs `MarkedVar`);
- Makes all of the backends use the same `MarkedVar` to string converter: this is the one previously used only for HSF.  This means Z3 output will use `VfooA` instead of `foo!after`;
- Accidentally put the heap-explicit version of the lclist in with the above oops.
